description: A full-stack machine learning project demonstrating image classification using a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) trained on the CIFAR-10 dataset, deployed as a user-friendly web application with Python's Flask framework.

This repository contains an experimental trading-bot framework built around machine learning, computer vision and stochastic modelling, with the goal of helping evaluate stocks (undervalued / fairly valued / overvalued) and ultimately support automated trading decisions.

Official implementation of "Analysis of Influential Factors for the Prediction of YouTube Views Using Tree-based Machine Learning" (JDCS 2025)  a machine learning framework that predicts YouTube video views across categories using metadata and derived variables, and interprets key influencing factors through SHAP analysis.
Predict traffic accident severity using advanced machine learning and explainable AI, enhancing road safety with clear insights from comprehensive data analysis.

This project presents a complete end-to-end analytics framework developed for Blinkit, using 8,523 real transactional records to generate actionable business insights through data preprocessing, exploratory analysis, machine learning, and interactive dashboarding.
Enterprise graph machine learning framework for billion-scale graphs for ML scientists and data scientists.

PhaseForge is a framework for high-throughput alloy phase diagram prediction using machine learning interatomic potentials (MLIPs) integrated with ATAT and CALPHAD modeling. Includes tools for structure relaxation, molecular dynamics, and TDB generation.

A comprehensive Python framework for automated data analysis, machine learning, and AI-powered insights. Features AutoML, explainable AI (SHAP/LIME), time series forecasting, interactive dashboards, and automated report generation.
Python SHIELD Machine Learning Framework - is a custom framework for AI/ML development compatible with Cuda, XPU and CPU. It also supports DDP.

Machine learning framework predicting U.S. county-level opioid cost per capita (20132023) by integrating Pharmacy Benefit Management (PBM) levers and Social Determinants of Health (SDOH). Includes data pipelines, simulation code, and reproducible figures.

A machine learning framework analyzing transportation policy impacts on urban congestion in the Philippines using Temporal Fusion Transformer models and causal inference. Features an interactive dashboard for policy simulation and includes 7,430+ observations from 12 data sources.
Building a simple deep learning framework and some machine learning/deep learning models from scratch (pure Numpy and Pytorch)
SmallML is a three-layer Bayesian framework that enables small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) to build production-grade machine learning models despite having limited customer data.

A multi-level obfuscation framework (mild, moderate, strong) for privacy-preserving machine learning on network-traffic data. Includes dataset balancing, obfuscation scripts, TabNet models, baseline ML benchmarks, and reproducible experiments.

Mapping Alternate Scenarios of Forest Intactness (MASFI) is a cloud-based machine learning framework. It uses XGBoost regression and remote sensing data such as GEDI LiDAR to create high-resolution maps and statistics, supporting protected area planning and management.

Official implementation of our paper "Unsupervised Active Learning via Natural Feature Progressive Framework", currently under review at IEEE Transactions on Pattern Analysis and Machine Intelligence (TPAMI)

Machine learning framework to analyze correlations in PrizePicks betting. Includes data pipeline for player stats, regression and ML models for correlation, and visualizations to support strategy simulations using public sports databases.

This project is an **advanced multi-stage Bitcoin ECDSA signature analyzer and recovery system**.   It integrates **machine learning (XGBoost, LSTM, GAN)**, **reinforcement learning (Gym)**, and **genetic algorithms**   to automatically detect weak or reused nonces across blockchain transactions and attempt secure key reconstruction.

Build a credit risk prediction model and apply SHAP and LIME to explain global and local decisions. Compare both methods, analyze discrepancies, and produce an interpretable, regulator-friendly explanation framework for fair and transparent loan approvals.
Project that  uses CRISP-DM framework to develop an end-to-end machine learning system using the UCI Heart Disease (Cleveland) dataset.

QuantFolio is a C#-based multi-asset portfolio management framework that integrates data collection, cleaning, optimization, backtesting, and visualization. It supports machine learning models, risk analysis, and customizable strategies, with a modern GUI for building, testing, and comparing investment portfolios.
DeepMech: A Machine Learning Framework for Chemical Reaction Mechanism Prediction
A Machine-Learning Framework for Epileptic Seizure Identification using Bangalore EEG Data

This project is a web-based application developed using Python's Flask framework that utilizes Machine Learning to provide personalized medicine, diet, and precaution recommendations based on user-inputted symptoms. The system is designed to act as a preliminary health advisory tool.

Banks face frequent loan defaults, demanding robust risk management. This study builds a machine learning framework to predict credit defaults using structured financial data. It includes data preprocessing, model building, and fairness evaluation to ensure predictions are both accurate and socially equitable.

Machine Learning Framework for Identifying Lymph Node Metastasis Biomarkers in Breast Cancer. This repository provides an end-to-end workflow integrating differential expression analysis, machine learningbased feature selection, survival modelling, and external biological validation for robust biomarker discovery.
institutional-grade quantitative trading and portfolio management system that unifies machine learning, convex optimization, and derivatives pricing into a single Python-based framework

The Multi-Agent RLRM (Reinforcement Learning with Reward Machines) Framework is a library designed to facilitate the formulation of multi-agent problems and solve them through reinforcement learning. The framework supports the integration of Reward Machines (RMs), providing a modular and flexible structure for defining complex tasks.
A customized autograd framework for machine learning

A comprehensive machine learning framework for multi-step stock price forecasting using ensemble methods combining deep learning, statistical models, and gradient boosting. This project implements a sophisticated stock price forecasting system that combines multiple machine learning approache.

This code is an implementation of a simple chatbot using TensorFlow, which is machine learning framework developed by Google. The chatbot is trained using a neural network to classify user inputs into predefined intents and provide appropriate responses based on detected intent. The intents.json file is the data that we will provide to our chatbot

A full-stack AI-powered stock market prediction platform built using Django REST Framework (DRF) for the backend and React.js for the frontend. This project leverages machine learning models to analyze historical stock data and predict future trends, helping users make data-driven investment decisions.

The project Revolutionizing Agriculture: Machine Learning and Deep Learning Solutions for Enhanced Crop Quality and Weed Control is a web-based application built using the Django framework. It integrates machine learning models with a user-friendly interface to support farmers and service providers in making informed agricultural decisions..

A framework integrating sentiment analysis with machine learning enhances cyberbullying detection on social media. Optimized preprocessing and balanced penta-class data improve accuracy. Extra Trees achieved 95.38% accuracy and 0.95 F1, showing sentiment features boost classification performance.
Explainable machine learning framework for forecasting multi-factor risk outcomes across biological and quantitative data.
Data for the paper "A Machine Learning Framework for Harvesting and Harmonizing Cultural and Touristic Data", published in the "Information" Journal/MDPI
A pipeline framework for developing video and image processing application. Supports multiple GPUs and Machine Learning tooklits

A lightweight terminal-based chatbot built using a hybrid approach  combining rule-based responses with a machine learning intent classifier. This project demonstrates core concepts of AI, NLP, and chatbot design without requiring heavy frameworks or internet access.
A machine learning project using the FastAI deeplearning framework and timm library. The model used was efficientnet_b0, trained on real-world healthy and diseased tomato leaf images.

This project demonstrates a quantum machine learning classification using Qiskit framework. Specifically, it builds quantum support vector machine (QSVM) models on classical datasets (e.g., breast cancer and heart disease) and explores quantum kernels and variational quantum classifiers (VQC) to classify data into distinct classes.

An opinionated machine learning framework.

Attention-guided deep learning framework for multi-class brain tumor classification using MRI scans. Combines EfficientNetB3 with CBAM for high accuracy (99.29%) and integrates Explainable AI (HiResCAM) for visual interpretability of predictions.

A foundational MLOps framework designed to operationalize the machine learning lifecycle using MLflow. This project establishes a standardized pipeline for experiment tracking, model versioning, and reproducible deployment.

Methodological framework for low-cost sensor calibration and air quality monitoring. Public repository developed as part of a PhD research on signal processing and machine learning for environmental metrology.

End-to-end machine learning pipeline for synthetic SNP data. Includes data simulation, preprocessing, model training (Logistic Regression, Random Forest, XGBoost), evaluation metrics, and visualizations. Ethical, reproducible framework for genomic prediction research.

Stroke Prediction with Explainable AI: A robust machine learning framework for predicting stroke risk using classical models, focusing on handling class imbalance and providing clinical interpretability with SHAP.

A real-time Digital Twin framework for Predictive Maintenance (PdM) of rotating machinery. Uses MQTT for live sensor data streaming, Streamlit for dashboard visualization, and Machine Learning models (Random Forest/LSTM) to predict Remaining Useful Life (RUL) and detect anomalies.
Adversarial Machine Learning Defense Framework

A modular machine learning framework for building, training, and evaluating regression models on multivariate time-series data. Includes preprocessing utilities, sliding-window generation, custom model pipelines, feature selection, and performance visualization.
A differentiable ray tracer using the PyTorch machine-learning framework in Python.

This project implements an **AI-driven cryptanalysis framework for ECDSA**, combining: -  **Genetic Algorithms** -  **Machine Learning (XGBoost, LSTM, TensorFlow)** -  **Simulated Annealing Optimization** -  **Reinforcement Learning Environment (OpenAI Gym)** -  **Linear and Reuse Nonce Detection** -  **Hybrid AI-supervised attacks**

Accent Converter is an AIpowered Django web application that processes audio files, performs accent conversion using machine learning models, and generates bilingual subtitles. It combines speech processing, transliteration, and a scalable backend with a simple, interactive frontend for accessibility.

Smart Flight Booking App is an intelligent flight reservation platform built with React.js and Django REST Framework that uses machine learning for price prediction, enabling users to seamlessly search, compare, and book flights through a secure, responsive, and visually appealing interface.

A framework for evaluating explainable AI (XAI) methods in drug discovery using multiple machine learning architectures. This repository implements three distinct model architectures (CNN, Random Forest, and RGCN) and provides a hierarchical four-tier evaluation framework for assessing the quality and reliability of their explanations.
Building machine learning algorithms from the ground up using Python. No frameworksjust pure implementations to understand the fundamentals.
Sum-of-Gaussians Neural Network (SOG-Net) is a lightweight and versatile framework for integrating long-range interactions into machine learning force field.

This project implements a handwritten digit recognizer using both TensorFlow and PyTorch frameworks to classify digits from the MNIST dataset. It provides a direct comparison of the performance and training characteristics between the two popular machine learning libraries.
Machine Learning based photo attendance framework

Dml (Decentralized Machine Learning) is an open-source framework designed to enable secure, verifiable, and collaborative AI model computation across decentralized networks.  It combines machine learning, blockchain, and zero-knowledge verification to ensure that every model inference or training process is both **trustless** and **provably correct

This project presents an AI-Driven IoT Framework designed to automate the process of fruit detection, ripeness classification, and autonomous plucking in modern smart farms. By integrating computer vision, machine learning, robotic control, and IoT connectivity, the system aims to improve harvesting efficiency, reduce labor dependency.

A next-generation AutoML construction framework that lets developers, researchers, and ML engineers design, evolve, and orchestrate machine learning pipelines as modular systems  not pre-built black boxes.

MetaMorph is an open-source framework that leverages the power of Large Language Models (LLMs) to process, extract, and transform messy, unstructured, or heterogeneous columns of metadata into structured, machine-readable formats to enhance machine learning pipelines and predictive models across any domain.
